registries.cfg — package registry configuration

LOCATION
  /etc/registries.cfg

FORMAT
  return {
    {
      name        = "<short id>",
      url         = "https://<host>/<path>",
      trusted_keys = { "<ed25519-pub-hex>", ... },
    },
    ...
  }

DESCRIPTION
  pkg(1) consults this list when resolving a package id. Multiple
  entries are queried in order; the first registry that knows the id
  wins. Each registry hosts an index.cfg listing available packages
  and one manifest.cfg + payload.tar per package.

  trusted_keys are Ed25519 public keys whose signatures over a
  manifest are accepted as authentic. Unsigned packages are only
  installable when no key is configured for the originating
  registry.

EXAMPLES
  return {
    { name = "official", url = "https://ocos.example.org/pkg",
      trusted_keys = { "abcd…" } },
    { name = "local",    url = "http://10.0.0.5:8080" },
  }

SEE ALSO
  pkg(1)
